 and sophisticated analyses of how we think, act, and conceive of ourselves. For James, making a habit of experimenting with life's myriad opportunities is not just a way to counter thinking that has grown too rigid, but a crucial precondition for making the most of one's life and self.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aApplied ethics. 0aLife. 0aPhilosophy. 0aPragmatism. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aPhilosophy : American Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPsychology : Psychology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849328240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493282423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493282/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles